    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm not 100% sure what you mean here.\r\n\r\nInactivity leaks continue to occur in state transitions even if justification/finality is not occurring. So yes, inactivity leaks can happen when 1/3 are offline. \r\n\r\nThis is because the chain building mechanism can remain live even if the finality mechanism is not. This is important because if a portion of the validators are permanently (or a long time) offline, the inactivity leak can ensure that the online portion can eventually become a 2/3 majority and finalize",
